By Emmanuel Oloniruha Abuja  – The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has commiserated with the government and people of Benue state over the tragic boat mishap, which claimed some lives.PDP’s National Publicity Secretary, Mr Kola Ologbondiyan, in a statement on Wednesday in Abuja, said that the party was deeply grieved by the traumatising incident.He said that the mishap brought pain, sorrow and untold anguish to families whose loved ones, particularly, children, died in the incident.“Our party mourns. Our thoughts and prayers go out to the bereaved, particularly the policemen of MOPOL 13 Barracks, whose children and relatives were among those who lost their lives.“The PDP shares in their grief and prays God to give them the fortitude to bear the loss,” he said.Ologbondiyan condoled with Gov. Samuel Ortom, the Evangelical Church Winning All (ECWA) as well as the people of Benue state and prayed God to grant eternal rest to the faithful departed.“The party urges all people of faith across the country to supplicate for our fatherland at this trying time, lamenting that the nation has witnessed a lot of tragedies and deaths in recent time,” he said. (NAN) By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post)  - National leadership of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) and the PDP Presidential Campaign Organization (PPCO) lament the death of its loyal and dedicated members of our great party and other Nigerians in a ghastly motor accident in Benue State. The party bemoans the… December 29, 2018 In "News" By Emmanuel Oloniruha Abuja -   The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has commiserated with the government and people of Lagos state, particularly the families of the victims of the Otedola Bridge petrol tanker explosion. PDP in a statement issued by its National Publicity Secretary, Mr Kola Ologbondiyan on Friday in… June 29, 2018 In "News" Ekweremadu Mourns Suntai June 28, 2017 In "News"